<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="miscellaneous" id="idb9487ad1-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prohibition of 9-Digit ZIP Code</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/97/35/tXVII/s1726">Pub. L. 97–35, title XVII, § 1726</ref>, <date date="1981-08-13">Aug. 13, 1981</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/95/761">95 Stat. 761</ref>, prohibited Postal Service from implementing ZIP code system using more than 5 digits before <date date="1983-10-01">Oct. 1, 1983</date>, and prohibited executive agencies from taking action to conform mailing procedures to ZIP code system using more than 5 digits during the period from <date date="1981-08-13">Aug. 13, 1981</date> to <date date="1982-12-31">Dec. 31, 1982</date>.</p>
</note>
